PHISHING EMAIL SAMPLE ANALYSIS – SAMPLE 3


Subject:
Google Security Alert – Suspicious Login Attempt

Sender Email:
security@google.com

Greeting:
Dear User,


EMAIL MESSAGE

We detected a suspicious sign-in attempt on your Google
account from an unknown device and location.

For your security, we recommend verifying your account
information immediately.

Please confirm your identity by visiting the secure
verification page below:

http://google-account-security-check.com

If you do not verify your account within the next
12 hours, your account access may be temporarily
restricted to protect your data.

Thank you for helping us keep your account secure.

Google Security Team


PHISHING INDICATORS IDENTIFIED

1. Suspicious Verification Link
The link "http://google-account-security-check.com"
is not an official Google domain. Legitimate Google
security pages normally use domains like
https://accounts.google.com.

2. Urgent Security Warning
The email pressures the user to act quickly by
claiming suspicious login activity and threatening
account restriction.

3. Generic Greeting
The message begins with "Dear User" instead of the
recipient's actual name.

4. External Verification Page
The email asks the user to verify account details
through an external link rather than through the
official Google website.


EMAIL CLASSIFICATION
Type: Phishing Email
Risk Level: HIGH


ANALYSIS SUMMARY

This email attempts to impersonate Google's security
team to create fear about unauthorized account access.
The attacker tries to trick the user into clicking a
malicious verification link.

If the victim enters their Google login credentials on
the fake website, the attacker can capture the username
and password and gain unauthorized access to the account.

Users should always verify security alerts by logging
into their account through the official Google website
instead of clicking links in emails.
